The paper deals with optimization techniques for finding sparse solutions to systems of polynomial equations, which is a problem that can be applied in various fields such as signal processing, machine learning, and computer vision. Therefore, the paper can be categorized under cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of linear algebra and optimization techniques, which can be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
